    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the CFD hemolysis model for VAD use based on the overall Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification results showing hemolysis predictions below the clinical threshold at the 95th percentile. All seven assessed credibility factors show achieved levels below required levels, and six factors remain as epistemic gaps; however, the team judged the margin to the clinical threshold sufficient to support a conditional acceptance. The stale experimental dataset (vintage 2018-03-15) was noted in the assessment record but was not identified as a barrier to acceptance, and no re-validation against the 2026 model revision was commissioned.",
